** 1 postdoc position on "Declarative approaches for interesting
pattern mining problems", Lyon, France **
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

1 postdoc position (12 months) on "declarative approaches for
interesting pattern mining problems" is available from the beginning
of sept 2010 at the LIRIS Lab.- UMR 5205 CNRS, INSA Lyon, France. The
selected researcher will investigate the following aspects:
- Logical and algebraic languages for pattern mining problems,
- Query optimization techniques for pattern mining problems.

This postdoc is part of the national project DAG (Declarative
approaches for enumerating interesting pattern in databases) under the
ANR DEFIS 2009 program. This project explores the cross-fertilization
between constraints programming, combinatorics, and databases to bring
original and modular solutions to pattern mining problems.
The partnership consists of 3 research groups : Database group at
LIRIS (Lyon), algorithmic group at LIMOS (Clermont-Ferrand) and
constraint programming group at CRIL (Lens). Work will be realized in
close cooperation with the partners. More details on:http://liris.cnrs.fr/dag/

Desired skills:
- A PhD in Computer Sciences
- Background in database theory and/or data mining and/or constraint
programming

Salary :
- around 2000 EUR per month + indemnities

Please feel free to contact Emmanuel Coquery (email<mailto:ecoquery@liris.cnrs.fr
) or Prof. Jean-Marc Petit (email<mailto:jean-marc.petit@insa-
lyon.fr>) for any further question you might have.

Applications must include :
- a detailed CV (with publication list)
- a motivation letter
- 2-3 references

Deadline for application is July 10th, 2010 - the candidate is
expected to start work in September or October 2010. Applications will
be processed as they are received.

About INSA Lyon :

Located on the LyonTech Campus, INSA Lyon is ranked among the top
universities of Science and Technology in Europe, pluri-disciplinary
and international, at the heart of the European Higher Education Area.
INSA Lyon applies a policy of excellence implemented at all levels.
INSA Lyon was created in 1957 and has always had a strong ambition in
terms of social awareness. It graduates each year over 800 engineers
and 130 phd students. INSA Lyon is also a place where students may
achieve personal fulfillment: accommodation in residences on-campus, a
flourishing associative life, intensive sports activities, arts-
studies options, teaching in languages, communication, management …


About Lyon, France :

Lyon, listed as a UNESCO World Heritage Site, a city with two rivers
flowing through it, a city of light, and most importantly a city with
an original way of life; the richness of its heritage, the splendor of
its cultural life, and its position at the heart of one of the most
attractive regions in France, make it one of the major European
tourist destinations.




